reviews.text:
A lovely place. They seem to be strimming too much and too many dogs ......
 but it's still a great place to see butterflies plants  birds,  and the odd toad or lizard.
Lovely place n great cafe with lovely staff
Suitable for families, young and old. Pet friendly too. Organic vege for sale on Sat and Sundays.

The most well kept and oldest lychee garden in Hong Kong is here. Free parking when you are able to get a space. Sadly every other originally well-intended setups have not been attended to for years. Even the vegetable and other farm patches are left there with weed overgrown. Many people are using the place simply as a dog park.

A spacious nature reserve. Easily accessible by bus or minibus. If you choose to go there by car in weekends, make sure u have to arrive early. Otherwise you have to wait for long. 
There’s also a small stall selling local fruits and vegetables.

reviews.text: 上月曾到訪，當時好不愉快，被約30多個講普通話人，硬佔了兩張長檯，當私化妝間走來走去，大聲叫囂，聽聞早上十點多就到達，只叫３杯飲品，直到一點我地到場，無位只有企等，店員叫佢地走，點都唔走，之後，我地見有化完裝人比錢，有人收錢，原來在做生意，話要報警，佢地至拉喼走，到公園繼續 ！
地方寬敞，可以慢慢享用。
我未試過食物，有户外坐位，可帶狗狗。
I茶座氣氛好慢慢觀賞田園和帶毛孫去行草園
咖啡三十幾蚊杯 同pacific coffee價錢差不多
